    <p>Dr. Herman Taylor is one of the most influential researchers in understanding cardiovascular disease in African Americans. As former director of the Jackson Heart Study - the largest single-site study of cardiovascular disease in African Americans - he has generated critical insights into why Black Americans have higher rates of heart disease and what can be done about it.</p>

    <p>His work emphasizes that heart disease disparities cannot be understood through biology alone; social determinants of health, structural racism, and community factors are central to the story.</p>
